  "prompt": "Is there an app that gives you recipes based on what you have in the fridge?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several apps that can help you find recipes based on the ingredients you have in your fridge. Some popular options include:\n\n1. **SuperCook**: This app allows you to input the ingredients you have on hand and generates a list of recipes you can make with them.\n\n2. **BigOven**: Along with traditional recipe searching, BigOven has a \"Use Up Leftovers\" feature that lets you enter ingredients and find recipes accordingly.\n\n3. **Cookpad**: This app is community-driven, where users can share their own recipes. You can search for recipes based on specific ingredients.\n\n4. **Yummly**: In addition to offering personalized recipe recommendations, Yummly allows you to filter recipes based on the ingredients you have.\n\n5. **Tasty**: Known for its cooking videos, Tasty also has a recipe finder that lets you search by ingredients.\n\nThese apps typically have user-friendly interfaces and can help reduce food waste by making use of ingredients you already have.",
